The longest documentary ever? At least the longest we have made, almost 7 1/2 hours, 
showing every minute of the scenic train ride between Bergen on the Norwegian west coast, 
crossing the mountains to the capital of Oslo.

Bergensbanen is 100 years in 2009, and the documentary was a wild idea from 
NRK staff that came through, and was, surprisingly, a big success.
